Developing and implementing SIEM detection queries in Splunk to identify malicious activity within the SOC environment.

Key focus areas included:

Detecting brute force login attempts on /DVWA/login.php
Identifying port scanning and enumeration behaviour
Flagging abnormal authentication patterns and repeated HTTP POST requests
Creating threshold-based alerts (e.g., more than 5 login attempts per minute per IP)
Reducing false positives through query refinement and tuning

Example Splunk query used:

index=main "POST /DVWA/login.php"
| bin _time span=1m
| stats count by _time, clientip
| where count > 5


